[{"id": "571bbf78-4ce5-4634-aa5e-b03c667ee34a", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: kelly sits alone at lunch with her headphones on. random bits of food hit her occasionally.\nASSISTANT: The canteen buzzed against her headphones\u2014not loud enough to block completely, but muted, distant, like hearing the world from underwater. Kelly picked at the edge of her sandwich, tearing off a small piece of crust, rolling it between her fingers. The bread was stale. School lunches always were.\n\nSomething small and hard struck her shoulder.\n\nShe didn't look up. Her hand kept moving\u2014tap, tap, tap against her thigh under the table, a rhythm she didn't consciously choose. Another projectile bounced off her headphone cup with a soft plastic sound and skittered across the table. A pea. She watched it roll to a stop near her tray.\n\nThree tables away, laughter. She could see them in her peripheral vision\u2014uniforms like hers, faces she didn't know. Didn't want to know. One of them was reaching for something else on their tray.\n\nA chip landed in her hair. She felt it lodge near her ear, the slight weight of it, grease cooling against her scalp. Her fingers twitched toward it, then stopped. If she acknowledged it, they'd keep going. If she ignored it, they'd keep going. There was no winning move, so she made none\u2014just sat, and picked at her sandwich, and let her hand tap against her leg while the noise of the canteen pressed in around the edges of her silence.\n\nAnother pea hit her arm. Then another.\n\nShe turned a page of the book she hadn't been reading.", "embedding": [-0.03533914312720299, -0.03983664512634277, 0.12339871376752853, -0.024930255487561226, 0.07388387620449066, -0.037894703447818756, 0.1533592790365219, -0.0015263750683516264, 0.031800106167793274, 0.019912144169211388, 0.07857822626829147, -0.007450351491570473, 0.0006769876927137375, -0.013051450252532959, -0.07637376338243484, -0.02147534489631653, 0.060119036585092545, 0.07136239856481552, -0